It can be tough to admit when we're not feeling up to certain activities or responsibilities. In your case, it seems like you're taking steps to preserve your mental health, even if that means missing out on some things right now.

It's not uncommon to experience a dip in motivation and performance when feeling overwhelmed. Your practice scores and energy levels will fluctuate, but they're not the sole measures of your worth or potential. Outside of academics and extracurriculars, remember to engage in things that bring you joy.

Things like making art, going for a walk, or having a funny conversation with someone else can help break up those not-so-fun times.&#x20;

I know it's a lot to swallow, but everything you're experiencing is valid and important. Keeping up with the pressures of being a high achiever and dealing with your mental health can be incredibly challenging. I hope you take things one step at a time and prioritize how you're feeling.&#x20;

A lot of people are skeptical of synchronicities, but the personal meaning we attach to such moments can be incredibly powerful. Notice when these "extra" coincidences occur and reflect on what's happening in your life at the time.

Sometimes these moments are nudges or signs to engage with certain themes or ideas. In your case, it's possible that this message resonated deeply with you today, reflecting your feelings about your own role and future.

Whatever the case, it's interesting that you took note. There's magic in the world when we keep our eyes open for it.&#x20;

It sounds like you've found yourself feeling "haunted" by these meaningful coincidences and glitches more and more.

